Narrow;font-size:12pt;">Capitalized interest decreased $9</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million sequentially to $40</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million due primarily to the commencement of operations 
of the newbuild drillships. </font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">Interest income was $4</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million, compared with $6</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million in the prior quarter.</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">Cash flows from operating activities were $2</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">07&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million, compared with $631</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million in the prior quarter. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">The decline was largely related to early contract 
termination fees that primarily impacted the first</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">quarter of 2016.</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">Capital expenditures totaled $458</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million, up from $368</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">million in the prior quarter. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">The increase was primarily associated with the 
company&#x2019;s newbuild program</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital expenditures in the 
second&nbsp;quarter of</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">2016</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;"> 
includ</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">ed</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;"> shipyard payments </font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">primarily </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">on the 
contracted newbuild, ultra-deepwater drillships </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-style:italic;font-
size:12pt;">Deepwater</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-style:italic;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-style:italic;font-

Narrow;font-size:12pt;">and </font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial
Narrow;font-style:italic;font-size:12pt;">Deepwater</font><font

Narrow;font-style:italic;font-size:12pt;">Conqueror</font><font

</p>

<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-

<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.6pt 12pt 27pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
weight:bold;font-size:12pt;">About Transocean</font>
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">Transocean is a leading international provider of offshore contract 
drilling services for oil and gas wells. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">The company specializes in technically demanding sectors
of the global offshore drilling business with a particular focus on deepwater 
and harsh environment drilling services, and believes that it operates one of 
the most versatile offshore drilling fleets in the world.</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">Transocean owns or has partial ownership interests</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;"> in, and 
operates a fleet of 60&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">mobile offshore drilling units consisting of 
29</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">ultra-deepwater floaters, seven</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">harsh-environment floaters, four</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">deepwater floaters, 10</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">midwater floaters and 10</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">high-specification jackups. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">In addition, the company has five</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">ultra-deepwater drillships and five</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">high-specification jackups under construction or under 
contract to be constructed.</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">For more information about Transocean, please visit: </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">www.deepwater.com</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">.</font>

family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">

<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 27.35pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">This press release, or referenced documents, do not constitute an 
offer to sell, or a solicitation of an offer to buy, any securities, and do not 
constitute an offering prospectus within the meaning of article 652a or article 
1156 of the Swiss Code of Obligations. </font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">Investors must 
rely on their own evaluation of Transocean and its securities, including the 
merits and risks involved. </font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;">Nothing contained herein is, or shall be 
relied on as, a promise or representation as to the future performance of 
Transocean</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;">.</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.6pt 12pt 27pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.6pt 12pt 27pt;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
weight:bold;font-size:12pt;">Notes</font>
</p>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;margin:0pt 
48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<p style="border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
<font style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;font-
size:12pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;;"> (1)</font>
</p>
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
<p style="border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;margin:0pt 
48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">Annual Effective Tax Rate is defined as income tax 
expense from continuing operations, excluding various discrete items (such as 
changes in estimates and tax on items excluded from income before income taxes),
divided by income from continuing operations before income tax expense excluding
gains and losses on sales and similar items pursuant to the accounting standards
for income taxes and estimating the annual effective tax rate. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;color:#000000;">See the accompanying schedule
entitled &#x201C;Supplemental Effective Tax Rate 
Analysis.&#x201D;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 45.35pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9
;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none
#D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 
12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
size:12pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;;"> (2)</font>
<font style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;font-
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none
#D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 
12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">Revenue efficiency is defined as actual contract 
drilling revenues for the measurement period divided by the maximum revenue 
calculated for the measurement period, expressed as a 
percentage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maximum revenue is defined as the greatest amount of 
contract drilling revenues the drilling unit could earn for the measurement 
period, excluding amounts related to incentive provisions. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;color:#000000;">See the accompanying schedule
entitled &#x201C;Revenue Efficiency.&#x201D;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9
;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none
#D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 
12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
size:12pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;;"> (3)</font>
<font style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;font-
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none
#D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 
12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">Rig utilization is defined as the total number of 
operating days divided by the total number of rig calendar days in the 
measurement period, expressed as a percentage. </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;color:#000000;">See the accompanying schedule
entitled &#x201C;Utilization.&#x201D;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9
;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-
size:12pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;;"> (4)</font>
<font style="margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;font-
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;margin:0pt 48.95pt 0pt 0pt;">
<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">Effective Tax Rate is defined as income tax expense 
for continuing operations divided by income from continuing operations before 
income taxes. </font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:12pt;color:#000000;">See the accompanying schedule
entitled &#x201C;Supplemental Effective Tax Rate Analysis</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-
size:12pt;color:#000000;">&#x201D;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</font>
</p>

New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-

</p>

9pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;">(2) Rig utilization is defined as the total number of operating days 
divided by the total number of available rig calendar days in the measurement 
period, expressed as a percentage.</font>

<div><hr style="border-

align="left"></hr></div>
<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 
9pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;">(3) Revenue efficiency is defined as actual contract drilling 
revenues for the measurement period divided by the maximum revenue calculation 
for the measurement period, expressed as a percentage.</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:9pt;"> Maximum revenue is defined as the greatest amount of 
contract drilling revenues the drilling unit could earn for the measurement 
period, excluding amounts related to incentive provisions.</font>
</p>

Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;">

<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;">
<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-
justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size:9pt;;"> (1)</font>
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">Our estimates change as we file tax returns, settle 
disputes with tax authorities or become aware of other events and include 
changes in (a) deferred taxes, (b) valuation of allowances on deferred taxes and
(c) other tax liabilities. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 
0pt 6pt;">
justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none 
#D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-
size:9pt;;"> (2)</font>
<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-
</p>
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 
0pt 6pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">The three </font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">and six </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">months </font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">ended June</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">3</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">0</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">, 201</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">6</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;"> includes $(</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">22</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial 
Narrow;font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">) million of additional tax expense 
(benefit) reflecting the catch-up effect of an increase (decrease) in the annual
effective tax rate from the previous quarter estimate</font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 
0pt 6pt;">
<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-
justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none 
#D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-
size:9pt;;"> (3)</font>
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 
0pt 6pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">Effective Tax Rate is income tax expense for continuing
operations, divided by income from continuing operations before income 
taxes</font><font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%;" cellpadding="0"
cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-
size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt; 
display: inline;">
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;">
<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-
justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;font-
family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size:9pt;;"> (4)</font>
</p>
size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-
<p style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-
ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;color:#000000;">Annual Effective Tax Rate is income tax expense for 
continuing operations, excluding various discrete items (such as changes in 
estimates and tax on items excluded from income before income taxes) divided by 
income from continuing operations before income tax expense excluding gains and 
losses on sales and similar items pursuant to the accounting standards for 
income taxes and estimating the annual effective tax 
rate.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 8pt;line-height:107.92%;font-family:Times
New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 9pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
size:9pt;"></font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.5pt;text-align:center;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;">
weight:bold;"></font></p></div><div style="margin-left:5.88235294117647%;margin-
right:5.88235294117647%;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
<p><font size="1"> </font></p></div><div style="margin-
left:5.88235294117647%;margin-right:5.88235294117647%;"><hr align="center" 
style='background-color:#000000; border-width:0; color:#000000; height:2pt; 
lineheight:0; width:100%;'></hr><p style="page-break-
after:always">&nbsp;</p></div><div style="margin-left:5.88235294117647%;margin-
right:5.88235294117647%;"></div><div style="margin-
left:5.88235294117647%;margin-right:5.88235294117647%;"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt
0pt 1.5pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Times New 
Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;"><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-weight:bold;">Transocean Ltd. and Subsidiaries</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.5pt;text-align:center;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;">
weight:bold;">Non-GAAP Financial Measures and Reconciliations</font>
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.5pt;text-align:center;line-
height:100%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;">
<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-
weight:bold;">Adjusted Net Income and </font><font style="display:inline;font-
family:Arial Narrow;font-weight:bold;">Adjusted </font><font 
style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;font-weight:bold;">Diluted 
Earnings Per Share</font>
</p>
<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.5pt;text-align:center;line-

<font style="display:inline;font-family:Arial Narrow;">(in US$
millions, except per share data)</font>

<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-
